    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-11-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="277"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                <head>277. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                    the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Bolivia</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d277fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 824.10/11–3056. Confidential. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BEO1"
                            >Briggs</persName> and initialed by <persName corresp="#p_BMM1"
                            >Bernbaum</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1956</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>157. <gloss target="#t_IMF1">IMF</gloss> yesterday approved exchange and
                    stabilization plans presented by its mission as well as standby financing of up
                    to $7.5 million. No public announcement for present but <gloss target="#t_GOB1"
                        >GOB</gloss> officials here informed and of course all official
                    communications to <gloss target="#t_GOB1">GOB</gloss> on <gloss target="#t_IMF1"
                        >IMF</gloss> decision will be via Eder and Antezana.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d277fn2">
                        <persName>Franklin Antezana Paz</persName>, President of the Central Bank of
                        Bolivia.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Treasury will negotiate exchange agreement for $5 million. <gloss
                        target="#t_ICA1">ICA</gloss> will provide $10 million for stabilization,
                    principally in form purchase authorizations for <gloss target="#t_GOB1"
                        >GOB</gloss> imports in public sector. These funds will come from regular
                    $20 million aid appropriation.</p>
                <p>As part stabilization arrangements Inter-Agency Committee<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d277fn3">The committee consisted of representatives from the
                        Departments of Agriculture, the Treasury, and State, and <gloss
                            target="#t_IMF1">IMF</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_ICA1"
                        >ICA</gloss>.</note> has approved offer of Title I <gloss target="#t_PL1"
                        >PL</gloss> 480 program in approximate amount $6,750,000 including: 40,000
                    MT wheat, value $3 million; 15,000 MT flour, value $1.75 million; 900 MT edible
                    oils, value $350,000; 1,000 MT lard, value $370,000. Balance of commodity
                    composition still undetermined. This program supplements $9.7 million <gloss
                        target="#t_ICA1">ICA</gloss> funds committed and to be committed and is in
                    lieu further <gloss target="#t_ICA1">ICA</gloss> food imports.</p>
                <p>You may now inform <gloss target="#t_GOB1">GOB</gloss> of above arrangements as
                    basis inquiry whether Congressional approval required <gloss target="#t_PL1"
                        >PL</gloss> 480 agreement and where most expeditious negotiate and sign.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> Eder still negotiating NY banks for
                    additional $2.5 or $5 million, planning stabilization move <gloss
                        target="#t_ODECA1">Dec</gloss>. 8. End <gloss target="#t_FYI1"
                    >FYI</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Will advise when public announcement stabilization package planned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
